<doc>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates the type of information provided by the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/win32/Direct2D/direct2ddebuglayer-overview">Direct2D Debug Layer</a>.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>To receive debugging messages, you must install the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/win32/Direct2D/direct2ddebuglayer-overview">Direct2D Debug Layer</a>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso cref="D2D1_FACTORY_OPTIONS" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/win32/Direct2D/direct2ddebuglayer-overview">Direct2D Debug Layer</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL.D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>Direct2D does not produce any debugging output.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL.D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL_ERROR">
    <summary>
      <para>Direct2D sends error messages to the debug layer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL.D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL_WARNING">
    <summary>
      <para>Direct2D sends error messages and warnings to the debug layer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL.D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL_INFORMATION">
    <summary>
      <para>Direct2D sends error messages, warnings, and additional diagnostic information that can help improve performance to the debug layer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL.D2D1_DEBUG_LEVEL_FORCE_DWORD">
    <summary></summary>
  </member>
</doc>